# Copy to the project root as  .client-demo.env  and edit, then:
#   ./setupclientdemo
#
# Join your phone’s hotspot as a client and use a fixed IPv4 (stable URL for QR).
#
# Android hotspot (typical): WPA2 + subnet 192.168.43.0/24, gateway 192.168.43.1 — the
# defaults below match that. Set CLIENT_DEMO_PSK to the hotspot password shown on the phone.
# (iPhone uses a different subnet; see comments under CLIENT_DEMO_IPV4.)
#
# Hotspot password: most Android and iPhone personal hotspots use WPA2 (not “open”). If
# setup fails with “Secrets were required”, set CLIENT_DEMO_PSK. Leave PSK empty only for a
# genuinely open (no key) network.
# CLIENT_DEMO_PSK=
# (alias) CLIENT_DEMO_PASSWORD=
#
# --- Your hotspot SSID (must match the phone) ---
CLIENT_DEMO_SSID=Sophia Science Project
#
# NetworkManager connection name (no spaces; safe on disk)
CLIENT_DEMO_CONN_NAME=smartair-client
#
# Wi‑Fi interface (Raspberry Pi is usually wlan0; USB Wi‑Fi might be wlan1)
CLIENT_DEMO_IFACE=
#
# Static IPv4 (must match the *same* subnet as the hotspot).
# Android: usually 192.168.43.1 = gateway, /24, so e.g. 192.168.43.100/24 (below).
# If the page will not load, join once with DHCP, then:  ip -4 route; ip -4 a show wlan0
# iPhone / iPad: different range (usually 172.20.10.0/28) — not 192.168.43.x
CLIENT_DEMO_IPV4=192.168.43.100/24
CLIENT_DEMO_GW=192.168.43.1
CLIENT_DEMO_DNS=192.168.43.1
#
# Linux user that owns the project and will run the web app
CLIENT_DEMO_USER=pi
#
# Full URL for notes / QR (optional; used by generate-demo-qrs if you add hooks later)
# CLIENT_DEMO_URL=http://192.168.43.100:5001/
#
# App port (must match config.yaml server.port; default 5001; used for QR if set)
# SMARTAIR_PORT=5001
